Source: Everquest General Discussion Forums.<br>
<br>
I have performed 10 independant tests, 3 on green mobs, 4 on blue, and 3 on even cons. Every time a successful Instill Doubt is performed, the first backstab thrown fails to register. No frontstab credit, no missed backstab, no attack whatsoever. I believe this may be a bug due to the change going on with the mob at the moment of its &quot;fearing&quot;, perhaps the game doesn't take an update of the mobs sudden change. I have waited up to 7 seconds before attempting the backstab also, this seems to be the barrier, it will at least try to backstab after about 8 or so seconds. Please look into this, a Rogues only chance of surviving a one-on-one fight sometimes is this skill, and if one skill nullifies the other, we lose our effectiveness. I hope this isn't a planned effect, is it really plausible for a Rogue to solo to any extent with no opportunities to backstab in said fight? <br>
You're not going to like this, but... <br>
<br>
It's working as intended. <br>
<br>
This was done intentionally, there was no programming error here. <br>
<br>
- Alan <br>
