</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utelurinon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telurinon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/00 2:30:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1946.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/celondon/TelurinonClose.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alan on Backstab/Instill Doubt</span><hr size=1> I imagine this is tied to 'special attacks.'  Kicks, Slam, Bash and Backstab all fall into this same category.  Haste Spells (possibly items as well -- I don't have one yet, so can't test it) decrease the cycle time of these attacks.<br>
<br>
I think what happens is the 'kick' in Instill Doubt counts as a real kick, which would mean that all other special attacks are considered 'used' until it's cycle time is done.  If you are hasted, the cycle time is faster, resulting in a lesser delay time you have to wait for a successful backstab.<br>
<br>
At least, that is my theory.  Anyone else think this could be the case? <p><SELECT NAME="D1">
