<OPTION>Geez, how many characters do you think I have?</SELECT><br><b>Backstab Watch!</b><br><img src=http://www.geocities.com/celondon/BSWatch.jpg><BR><BR>Skating away on the thin ice of a new day.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulucutos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lucutos</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/00 3:31:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1946.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alan on Backstab/Instill Doubt</span><hr size=1> I'm quite positive that Telurinon has it correct.<br>
<br>
The kick on the instill doubt &quot;greys&quot; out backstab until it recycles.  This is ok I suppose, however as someone else mentioned it REALLY should actually grey out the backstab button.<br>
<br>
You'll notice if you totally fail an instill doubt (Your not scaring anyone) then you can backstab right away.  this is because you did not attempt a kick.<br>
<br>
I got a little upset the first time I realized what was happening, but I suppose it is sort of balancing.  If you think about it, we could easily get 2 and possibly 3 backstabs in per instill doubt success if we did not have to wait for 1 cycle.  As it is now I always get 1 attempt and rarely get 2.<br>
<br>
Someone get Vaslin or Kendrik to look into greying the backstab button out after Instill goes off though, then I'll be happy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center>
